WEBVTT

00:10.178 --> 00:11.512
- * ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR

00:11.545 --> 00:13.314
* ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX *

00:13.347 --> 00:14.515
* SHAKE IT, DUDE

00:14.548 --> 00:22.490
*

00:28.496 --> 00:29.730
* ONE, TWO, DO IT

00:29.763 --> 00:32.266
*

00:32.300 --> 00:33.601
* ONE, TWO, THREE

00:33.634 --> 00:35.436
- * FOUR, FOUR

00:35.469 --> 00:38.472
*

00:40.208 --> 00:43.144
[Washed Up Love plays]

00:43.177 --> 00:44.812
- WHOO!

00:44.845 --> 00:47.281
*

00:47.315 --> 00:48.482
- * FEEL ME WITH YOUR LOVE

00:48.516 --> 00:50.851
- YEAH!

00:50.884 --> 00:54.222
- WHOO!

00:54.255 --> 00:58.526
- * WITH YOUR LOVE

01:07.368 --> 01:09.603
- WHOO!

01:33.494 --> 01:36.297
[coins sliding]

01:45.639 --> 01:47.241
- [shudders]

01:48.842 --> 01:51.345
I LOST A SOCK
AND A PAIR OF SHORTS,

01:51.379 --> 01:52.646
BUT THE FUCK IF I'M GOING
BACK DOWN THERE

01:52.680 --> 01:56.884
WITH THE CRYPT-MASTER.

01:56.917 --> 01:58.752
BEN?
- UH, YEAH?

01:58.786 --> 02:00.621
- I SAID THERE WAS
THIS GUY DOWN THERE.

02:00.654 --> 02:02.890
THIS--

02:02.923 --> 02:05.559
THIS INCREDIBLY HOT GUY,

02:05.593 --> 02:07.395
AND I WAS BENDING OVER

02:07.428 --> 02:09.230
TO GET MY LAUNDRY
OUT OF THE DRYER,

02:09.263 --> 02:10.898
AND HE RIPPED OFF MY PANTS,

02:10.931 --> 02:12.366
AND HE FUCKED THE SHIT
OUT OF ME.

02:12.400 --> 02:13.501
[grunts]

02:13.534 --> 02:15.469
- UH-HUH.

02:19.673 --> 02:20.841
- [clears throat]
- HEY.

02:20.874 --> 02:22.643
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

02:22.676 --> 02:24.278
- I'M READING THE NEWSPAPER,
AND I'M NEARSIGHTED.

02:24.312 --> 02:25.913
SO I--
OH, THE CLASSIFIEDS. OH.

02:25.946 --> 02:28.416
- YEAH, I'M LOOKING
FOR AN APARTMENT, MICHAEL.

02:28.449 --> 02:31.319
- [groans] YOU ALREADY HAVE
AN APARTMENT,

02:31.352 --> 02:33.521
COMPLETE WITH APPLIANCES
AND HARDWOOD FLOORS

02:33.554 --> 02:35.389
AND A BUILT-IN BOYFRIEND.
- YEAH, I TOLD YOU.

02:35.423 --> 02:36.857
I THINK IT'S BEST
IF I HAVE MY OWN PLACE.

02:36.890 --> 02:40.428
- YEAH, AND I THINK
IT'S BEST THAT YOU STAY.

02:50.871 --> 02:52.940
- ARE YOU SURE YOU WOULDN'T
RATHER BE OUT WITH BRIAN?

02:52.973 --> 02:55.543
- [sighs]

02:55.576 --> 02:58.612
- [moaning]

02:58.646 --> 03:02.416
- WELL, I HAVE TO ADMIT,
IT IS TEMPTING.

03:02.450 --> 03:03.984
BUT THEN, I WOULD MISS OUT

03:04.017 --> 03:07.721
ON ALL THE PRE-SOAKING
AND SPIN-DRYING,

03:07.755 --> 03:08.989
AND NOT TO MENTION,

03:09.022 --> 03:12.226
HAVING THE HOTTEST MAN
IN PITTSBURGH

03:12.260 --> 03:15.663
TO HELP ME FLUFF AND FOLD.

03:23.537 --> 03:24.738
- HELP YOU
WITH THE CENTER CARNIVAL?

03:24.772 --> 03:26.340
ARE YOU
OUT OF YOUR FUCKING MIND?

03:26.374 --> 03:27.841
- I LIKE TO THINK NOT.

03:27.875 --> 03:29.477
- AFTER THE WAY
THEY SCREWED ME,

03:29.510 --> 03:30.478
THE ONLY THING I'D LIKE
TO HELP THE CENTER DO

03:30.511 --> 03:31.912
IS SELF-DESTRUCT.

03:31.945 --> 03:33.581
- WELL, THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT MIGHT HAPPEN

03:33.614 --> 03:34.848
IF WE DON'T BOOST
OUR CORPORATE SPONSORSHIP

03:34.882 --> 03:36.350
AND RAISE
A COUPLE HUNDRED THOUSAND.

03:36.384 --> 03:38.486
- IT'S NOT MY PROBLEM.

03:44.625 --> 03:45.726
- [clears throat]

03:45.759 --> 03:48.796
[Gus babbles]

03:48.829 --> 03:51.465
ANYONE ELSE IN THERE
I SHOULD KNOW ABOUT?

03:51.499 --> 03:53.934
- HOPEFULLY NOT BEFORE I DO.

03:53.967 --> 03:55.603
- LOOK, IT MAY NOT
BE YOUR PROBLEM.

03:55.636 --> 03:56.770
BUT IT'D BE
A VERY BIG PROBLEM

03:56.804 --> 03:58.339
FOR A LOT OF MEMBERS
OF OUR COMMUNITY

03:58.372 --> 03:59.740
IF WE HAD TO CUT
ON AIDS HOSPICE CARE

03:59.773 --> 04:00.808
OR THE HOMELESS TEEN SHELTER.

04:00.841 --> 04:02.476
ALL I'M ASKING

04:02.510 --> 04:04.378
IS FOR YOU TO VOLUNTEER
A FEW HOURS OF YOUR TIME

04:04.412 --> 04:06.380
TO HELP ORGANIZE
THIS FUND-RAISER.

04:06.414 --> 04:07.815
MAYBE CALL
A FEW OF YOUR CLIENTS

04:07.848 --> 04:09.383
AND SEE IF THEY'D BE
WILLING TO CONTRIBUTE.

04:09.417 --> 04:11.519
- OH, I-I DON'T DO
VOLUNTEER WORK.

04:11.552 --> 04:13.921
- OH, THANKS A LOT, BRIAN.

04:13.954 --> 04:15.489
HOPE I DIDN'T KEEP YOU
FROM ATTENDING

04:15.523 --> 04:18.626
TO MORE IMPORTANT THINGS.

04:18.659 --> 04:21.429
- HOWEVER, THE CENTER AND I
MAY BE ABLE

04:21.462 --> 04:23.564
TO COME TO SOME MORE...

04:23.597 --> 04:26.900
AMENABLE AGREEMENT?

04:26.934 --> 04:28.769
- THERE IS NO WAY
WE'RE WORKING WITH HIM.

04:28.802 --> 04:30.371
- IT'S OUT OF THE QUESTION.

04:30.404 --> 04:32.573
- I UNDERSTAND YOUR RELUCTANCE
TO GET INVOLVED.

04:32.606 --> 04:35.042
HOWEVER, IF HE'S WILLING
TO PUT PAST HOSTILITIES ASIDE,

04:35.075 --> 04:36.710
I SAY
WE SHOULD DO THE SAME.

04:36.744 --> 04:41.048
- JUST WHAT EXACTLY
IS MR. KINNEY OFFERING TO DO?

04:41.081 --> 04:44.385
- ORGANIZE THE EVENT, BRING IN
CORPORATE SPONSORSHIP...

04:44.418 --> 04:46.387
- I SAY WE'RE DOING FINE
WITHOUT HIM.

04:46.420 --> 04:50.524
- IF YOU CALL SELLING
40 TICKETS "DOING FINE."

04:50.558 --> 04:51.959
BRIAN'S PUT TOGETHER
A PROPOSAL

04:51.992 --> 04:53.527
TO GIVE THE CARNIVAL
A BIT MORE EDGE.

04:53.561 --> 04:55.429
OOPS.
- EDGE?

04:55.463 --> 04:57.931
- HE'S ALSO CONTACTED
A FEW OF HIS CLIENTS.

04:57.965 --> 05:00.401
AND THEY'VE AGREED
TO SPONSOR THE EVENT

05:00.434 --> 05:03.571
AND MATCH ANY FUNDS WE RAISE
UP TO $100,000.

05:06.707 --> 05:09.477
- PLEASE EXTEND
TO MR. KINNEY

05:09.510 --> 05:11.545
THE CENTER'S GRATITUDE

05:11.579 --> 05:13.447
FOR VOLUNTEERING HIS TIME
AND EFFORT.

05:13.481 --> 05:14.815
- [giggles excitedly]

05:14.848 --> 05:18.419
- WELL, HE'S...
NOT EXACTLY VOLUNTEERING.

05:18.452 --> 05:20.688
- HE WANTS 20%
OFF THE TOP.

05:20.721 --> 05:23.123
- HE EXPECTS US TO PAY HIM?
FOR FUND-RAISING?

05:23.156 --> 05:25.459
- IS HE KIDDING?
- WELL, HIS FEELING IS,

05:25.493 --> 05:28.128
"WOULD YOU RATHER HAVE
100% OF NOTHING

05:28.161 --> 05:33.601
OR 80% OF MORE THAN YOU EVER
FUCKING DREAMED OF?"

05:33.634 --> 05:39.006
- * GOTTA GET OUT
ON MY OWN *

05:39.039 --> 05:40.708
* I'VE HAD ENOUGH
OF THE CROWD *

05:40.741 --> 05:43.611
* GOTTA GET OUT
ON MY OWN *

05:43.644 --> 05:45.579
* PUSHED
AND KNOCKED AROUND *

05:45.613 --> 05:47.648
* I'VE HAD ENOUGH OF THE CROWD
- HMM.

05:47.681 --> 05:49.149
- * GOTTA GET OUT ON MY OWN

05:49.182 --> 05:51.519
- SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?
SHOULD I BUY IT?

05:51.552 --> 05:53.153
- $30,000?

05:53.186 --> 05:54.988
THAT'S A LOT OF MONEY
FOR AN OLD CAR.

05:55.022 --> 05:56.590
- IT'S NOT OLD.
IT'S A CLASSIC.

05:56.624 --> 05:58.158
- SO HOW DO YOU PLAN
ON PAYING FOR IT?

05:58.191 --> 05:59.893
- A LITTLE EXTRA CASH
JUST FELL IN MY LAP.

05:59.927 --> 06:01.729
- WELL, THAT'S
A SIZEABLE CHUNK OF CHANGE

06:01.762 --> 06:04.164
FOR BOYFRIEND REPLACEMENT
THERAPY.

06:04.197 --> 06:06.066
- I DON'T HAVE A BOYFRIEND.

06:06.099 --> 06:09.169
I'VE NEVER HAD A BOYFRIEND.
- RIGHT.

06:09.202 --> 06:10.738
THEN IT MUST BE
A MID-LIFE CRISIS.

06:10.771 --> 06:12.473
- I'M ONLY 30--
- 1.

06:12.506 --> 06:14.642
- AND SINCE I PLAN ON BEING DEAD
BY THE TIME I'M 39,

06:14.675 --> 06:16.076
THAT'S ONE ANNOYANCE
I WON'T HAVE TO DEAL WITH.

06:16.109 --> 06:17.678
- YEAH. I'LL BE SURE
TO REMIND YOU OF THAT

06:17.711 --> 06:20.681
ON YOUR 60TH BIRTHDAY.

06:20.714 --> 06:22.416
- COME ON, MIKEY.
IF WE LEAVE NOW,

06:22.450 --> 06:23.517
WE CAN BE IN NEW YORK
BY MIDNIGHT.

06:23.551 --> 06:26.053
- NO FUCKING WAY.

06:26.086 --> 06:27.888
BEN NEARLY MOVED OUT
BECAUSE OF YOU.

06:27.921 --> 06:31.058
- * OVER THE EDGE
OF THE WORLD *

06:31.091 --> 06:34.762
* DON'T STOP TO WONDER

06:34.795 --> 06:36.630
* WONDER WHAT IT MEANS

06:36.664 --> 06:38.666
[tires squeal]

06:40.200 --> 06:42.903
- JEAN, YOUR ORDER'S UP.
- OKAY.

06:42.936 --> 06:44.838
- IS THAT LOOK OF LONGING

06:44.872 --> 06:47.074
FOR ME
OR THE COCONUT CREAM?

06:47.107 --> 06:49.777
- [laughs]
NOW WOULDN'T YOU LIKE TO KNOW?

06:49.810 --> 06:51.512
- [chuckles]
WANT THE LAST BITE?

06:51.545 --> 06:53.080
- HELL, NO.

06:53.113 --> 06:55.649
I'M ALMOST AT THE POINT
WHERE I ACTUALLY HAVE A WAIST.

06:55.683 --> 06:57.551
OR HAVEN'T YOU NOTICED?

06:57.585 --> 06:59.553
- OH, I'VE NOTICED.

06:59.587 --> 07:01.188
- AND?

07:01.221 --> 07:03.924
- AND IT'S LOOKIN' GOOD.

07:03.957 --> 07:06.460
REAL GOOD.
- COME ON, DEB.

07:06.494 --> 07:07.528
[bell ringing]

07:07.561 --> 07:09.129
- UM...

07:09.162 --> 07:10.230
ORDER'S UP.

07:10.263 --> 07:12.065
- SEE YOU FRIDAY?
- YEAH.

07:12.099 --> 07:14.535
I'LL RESERVE A LANE.
- WHAT DO YOU SAY

07:14.568 --> 07:16.570
WE SKIP THE BOWLING
THIS WEEK,

07:16.604 --> 07:17.938
MAYBE HAVE
A LITTLE DINNER?

07:17.971 --> 07:20.140
- FRIDAY IS
3 GRAMS OF FISH

07:20.173 --> 07:22.743
AND 4 OUNCES
OF STEAMED KALE.

07:22.776 --> 07:23.944
- MMM!
MY FAVORITE.

07:23.977 --> 07:24.945
- [laughs]

07:24.978 --> 07:27.815
- AFTERWARDS WE CAN WATCH TV.

07:27.848 --> 07:29.116
- YEAH, WELL,
THE--THE--

07:29.149 --> 07:31.485
THE SET DOWNSTAIRS
IS STILL ON THE FRITZ.

07:31.519 --> 07:33.220
THE ONLY ONE
THAT'S WORKING

07:33.253 --> 07:34.888
IS THE ONE
IN MY BEDROOM.

07:34.922 --> 07:37.591
- I KNOW.

07:37.625 --> 07:41.094
[laughs]
- [chuckles]

07:41.128 --> 07:42.095
- BE RIGHT BACK.

07:42.129 --> 07:43.897
- [laughs]

07:43.931 --> 07:47.601
- THERE YOU GO.
- OOH, FOOD.

07:47.635 --> 07:49.570
- SO, DEB...

07:49.603 --> 07:51.104
WHAT'S IT LIKE,
DOING IT WITH A COP?

07:51.138 --> 07:52.740
- [chuckles]
DOES HE

07:52.773 --> 07:53.874
CONDUCT A STRIP SEARCH?

07:53.907 --> 07:54.975
- HANDCUFF YOU TO THE BED?

07:55.008 --> 07:56.844
- WORK YOU OVER
TILL YOU SING?

07:56.877 --> 07:59.980
- DO YOU KNOW
WHAT M.Y.O.B. STANDS FOR?

08:00.013 --> 08:04.785
MIND YOUR OWN
FUCKING BUSINESS.

08:04.818 --> 08:06.720
- SHOULDN'T THERE BE
AN "F" IN THERE?

08:06.754 --> 08:08.055
- HMM.

08:08.088 --> 08:09.256
- HI, BE RIGHT WITH YOU.

08:09.289 --> 08:10.591
[fingers snap]

08:10.624 --> 08:15.696
[indistinct conversation]

08:19.032 --> 08:22.002
- I HAVE A PROPOSITION.

08:22.035 --> 08:23.871
A BUSINESS PROPOSITION.

08:23.904 --> 08:26.139
- WHAT'D YOU HAVE IN MIND?
- A POSTER.

08:26.173 --> 08:28.742
SOMETHING HOT AND BRILLIANT

08:28.776 --> 08:30.744
AND SOMETHING BY TOMORROW?

08:30.778 --> 08:33.681
- [sighs]

08:33.714 --> 08:36.083
- I WOULDN'T ASK YOU IF
I DIDN'T THINK YOU COULD DO IT.

08:36.116 --> 08:37.885
- OR IF YOU WEREN'T DESPERATE.

08:37.918 --> 08:41.321
- YEAH, THAT TOO.

08:41.354 --> 08:42.790
- WHAT'S IT FOR?

08:42.823 --> 08:45.058
- IT'S FOR
THE CENTER CARNIVAL.

08:45.092 --> 08:47.060
- YOU FUCKING HATE
THE CENTER.

08:47.094 --> 08:50.030
- NOT WHEN THEY'RE PAYING ME.

08:50.063 --> 08:52.299
SO HOW MUCH DO YOU WANT?

08:52.332 --> 08:54.635
- IT'S FOR A GOOD CAUSE,
SO IT'S FREE.

08:54.668 --> 08:56.670
- CHRIST,
DIDN'T I TEACH YOU ANYTHING?

08:56.704 --> 08:57.671
- 500.

08:57.705 --> 08:59.306
- 200.
- 500.

08:59.339 --> 09:02.175
TAKE IT OR LEAVE IT.

09:02.209 --> 09:04.945
- I LIKE THE WAY
YOU DO BUSINESS.

09:08.215 --> 09:10.684
- YOU HAD THE PROCEDURE?

09:10.718 --> 09:12.786
- LIKE YOU SAID,
IT WAS NO BIG DEAL.

09:12.820 --> 09:14.121
HE DID IT IN THE OFFICE,

09:14.154 --> 09:15.956
ZAPPED ME WITH A LASER,
A COUPLE OF STITCHES--

09:15.989 --> 09:17.958
- BUT YOU SHOULD'VE TOLD ME.
I WOULD'VE COME.

09:17.991 --> 09:20.327
- IT WAS SOMETHING I HAD
TO DO ON MY OWN,

09:20.360 --> 09:21.962
LIKE BUNGEE JUMPING.

09:21.995 --> 09:23.931
- I HOPE THAT'S NOT NEXT.
[nervous chuckle]

09:23.964 --> 09:25.799
- I MEAN, FACE MY FEARS
HEAD-ON

09:25.833 --> 09:27.935
AND HOPE
I DON'T LAND SPLAT.

09:27.968 --> 09:30.070
- AND DID YOU LAND SPLAT?

09:30.103 --> 09:32.339
- EVERYTHING'S FINE.

09:32.372 --> 09:34.341
HE SAID I CAN GET PREGNANT
RIGHT AWAY.

09:34.374 --> 09:37.144
- OH.
MEL.

09:37.177 --> 09:39.212
- [sighs]
- MM.

09:39.246 --> 09:42.115
- OH.

09:42.149 --> 09:44.217
I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT.
I WAS--

09:44.251 --> 09:46.086
I WAS JUST USING IT
AS AN EXCUSE.

09:46.119 --> 09:47.955
- IT DOESN'T MATTER.
- IT MATTERS A LOT.

09:47.988 --> 09:50.357
BECAUSE I WANT
TO BE THE ONE

09:50.390 --> 09:52.225
TO CARRY OUR NEXT CHILD.

09:52.259 --> 09:55.629
- ARE YOU SURE?

09:55.663 --> 09:57.831
SO WE COULD HAVE
A LITTLE MELANIE?

09:57.865 --> 09:59.833
- OR MELVIN.
- BY NEXT CHRISTMAS?

09:59.867 --> 10:01.368
- HANUKKAH.
- AH!

10:01.401 --> 10:03.003
- [sighs]

10:03.036 --> 10:05.372
NOW ALL WE HAVE TO DO
IS PICK A DONOR.

10:05.405 --> 10:10.143
- I THOUGHT
WE ALREADY HAD ONE.

10:10.177 --> 10:12.012
- THERE'S NO FUCKING WAY

10:12.045 --> 10:14.014
BRIAN KINNEY'S FUCKING SPERM
ARE DOING THE BREASTSTROKE

10:14.047 --> 10:15.248
UP MY FALLOPIAN TUBE.

10:15.282 --> 10:17.718
- THEY DO
THE AUSTRALIAN CRAWL.

10:17.751 --> 10:19.286
I SPEAK FROM EXPERIENCE.

10:19.319 --> 10:20.754
- WELL,

10:20.788 --> 10:23.423
NOT AFTER ALL THE GRIEF
HE'S CAUSED US.

10:23.456 --> 10:25.759
WE ARE NOT MAKING
THE SAME MISTAKE TWICE.

10:25.793 --> 10:27.427
- I UNDERSTAND PERFECTLY
HOW YOU FEEL,

10:27.460 --> 10:29.296
BUT WHAT IF SOMETHING
WERE TO HAPPEN TO US?

10:29.329 --> 10:31.264
A FATAL ACCIDENT?
- BUNGEE JUMPING?

10:31.298 --> 10:33.867
- I'M SERIOUS. AT LEAST OUR KIDS
WOULD HAVE THE SAME FATHER.

10:33.901 --> 10:34.868
- OH, SOME FATHER.

10:34.902 --> 10:36.937
SELFISH, PROMISCUOUS.

10:36.970 --> 10:38.405
WHO KNOWS
IF HE'S EVEN NEGATIVE?

10:38.438 --> 10:40.340
- WELL, WHOEVER IT IS
WOULD HAVE TO BE TESTED.

10:40.373 --> 10:42.776
BUT THINK HOW GOOD
HE'S BEEN TO US AND TO GUS.

10:42.810 --> 10:44.344
ALWAYS THERE TO WRITE
A CHECK,

10:44.377 --> 10:47.014
PUT UP A SWING SET, AND SAVE
OUR WEDDING FROM DISASTER.

10:47.047 --> 10:49.950
HONESTLY, MEL,
HE'S NOT THE OLD BRIAN.

10:49.983 --> 10:51.018
HE'S CHANGED.

10:51.051 --> 10:52.452
AND BOTTOM LINE...

10:52.485 --> 10:57.024
WITHOUT HIM, OUR KIDS
WOULDN'T BE RELATED.

10:57.057 --> 10:59.760
[Gus babbles]

10:59.793 --> 11:01.228
[pop music]

11:01.261 --> 11:03.931
- [grunts]

11:03.964 --> 11:06.233
- WHO'S THE HOTTIE?

11:06.266 --> 11:08.235
- MY BOYFRIEND.

11:08.268 --> 11:10.170
- THE OTHER HOTTIE.

11:10.203 --> 11:12.072
- OOH, LOOKS LIKE TARZAN.

11:12.105 --> 11:14.041
- AND HE SOUNDS LIKE JANE.

11:14.074 --> 11:16.043
- I'D WARBLE LIKE
A COLORATURA

11:16.076 --> 11:17.811
IF I HAD PECS LIKE HIS.

11:17.845 --> 11:19.847
- WELL, SHOOT YOURSELF UP
WITH JUNGLE JUICE, AND YOU CAN.

11:19.880 --> 11:21.915
- WHAT, STEROIDS?

11:21.949 --> 11:23.350
- YEAH, I'M SURPRISED HIS LIVER
HASN'T FALLEN OUT

11:23.383 --> 11:24.451
OF HIS ASSHOLE.

11:24.484 --> 11:25.986
- NOT TO MENTION MOOD SWINGS

11:26.019 --> 11:27.187
AND HIS BALLS SHRINKING UP

11:27.220 --> 11:28.455
TO THE SIZE
OF TWO M&M PEANUTS.

11:28.488 --> 11:29.823
[giggles]

11:29.857 --> 11:30.958
- MOM,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

11:30.991 --> 11:32.192
- SAME THING YOU ARE.

11:32.225 --> 11:33.727
- CRUISING FOR A BLOW JOB?

11:33.761 --> 11:35.963
- JESUS, MA, YOU ALREADY
GO TO THE SAME BARS

11:35.996 --> 11:37.130
AND THE SAME CLUBS I DO.

11:37.164 --> 11:38.999
NOW YOU GOTTA COME
TO THE SAME GYM?

11:39.032 --> 11:41.334
CAN'T I HAVE ONE PLACE
IN THE WORLD THAT'S MY OWN?

11:41.368 --> 11:45.205
- SO YOU WANNA
BE WORK-OUT BUDDIES?

11:45.238 --> 11:53.080
*

11:53.113 --> 11:55.282
- LOOKING GOOD, GIRL.

11:55.315 --> 11:57.350
- BET YOUR PRIVATE DICK
THINKS SO TOO.

11:57.384 --> 11:59.352
- [laughs]
- I TOLD YOU,

11:59.386 --> 12:00.921
I HAVE NO INTENTION

12:00.954 --> 12:01.989
OF TURNING
THE MOST INTIMATE DETAILS

12:02.022 --> 12:03.957
OF MY PERSONAL LIFE
INTO GYM GOSSIP,

12:03.991 --> 12:05.358
LIKE YOU GAY GUYS.

12:05.392 --> 12:08.095
- IN OTHER WORDS,
YOU HAVEN'T DONE IT YET.

12:08.128 --> 12:10.831
- WELL, IT ISN'T
BECAUSE HE ISN'T INTERESTED.

12:10.864 --> 12:12.499
IT'S JUST BEEN
A WHILE SINCE I--

12:12.532 --> 12:14.401
I WORKED OUT.

12:14.434 --> 12:17.971
I WOULDN'T WANT
TO DISAPPOINT HIM.

12:18.005 --> 12:19.907
- WELL,

12:19.940 --> 12:22.242
IF ANYONE KNOWS
HOW TO PLEASE HIS MAN,

12:22.275 --> 12:24.878
IT'S EM.

